      "boundElements": [],
      "updated": 1748800000017,
      "link": null,
      "locked": false,
      "text": "PRODUCE:    producer.Produce(\"orders\", \"user:Alice\", \"order:1\")  →  hash(\"user:Alice\") % 4 = 2  →  PartitionLog[2].Append(msg)  →  offset = _log.Count = 7\n            ProduceResult { Topic=\"orders\", Partition=2, Offset=7 }  ←  permanent address for audit; at-least-once: retry until receipt received\n\nCONSUME:   Consumer A polls P0, P3  →  ReadFrom(committedOffset)  →  process each message (offset order)  →  CommitAll(maxOffset + 1)\n            crash before commit → re-process batch (at-least-once)  |  crash after commit → never re-process  |  consumers must be idempotent\n\nREBALANCE: AddConsumer(C): roster = [A, B, C], 4 partitions  →  Rebalance(): p % 3  →  A: [P0, P3]   B: [P1]   C: [P2]\n            C starts from committedOffset = 0 (replays full log)  |  idle consumer = hot standby for instant failover on peer crash\n\nCOMPACT:   profiles topic (IsCompacted=true)  →  LogCompactor.Compact(): Pass1 latest[key] wins  →  Pass2 strip tombstones (Value == null)\n            result = one msg per key · deleted keys absent  |  tombstone cancels earlier value before removal  |  new consumer replays current state from offset 0",
      "fontSize": 13,
      "fontFamily": 1,
      "textAlign": "left",
      "verticalAlign": "middle",
      "containerId": "legend",
      "originalText": "PRODUCE:    producer.Produce(\"orders\", \"user:Alice\", \"order:1\")  →  hash(\"user:Alice\") % 4 = 2  →  PartitionLog[2].Append(msg)  →  offset = _log.Count = 7\n            ProduceResult { Topic=\"orders\", Partition=2, Offset=7 }  ←  permanent address for audit; at-least-once: retry until receipt received\n\nCONSUME:   Consumer A polls P0, P3  →  ReadFrom(committedOffset)  →  process each message (offset order)  →  CommitAll(maxOffset + 1)\n            crash before commit → re-process batch (at-least-once)  |  crash after commit → never re-process  |  consumers must be idempotent\n\nREBALANCE: AddConsumer(C): roster = [A, B, C], 4 partitions  →  Rebalance(): p % 3  →  A: [P0, P3]   B: [P1]   C: [P2]\n            C starts from committedOffset = 0 (replays full log)  |  idle consumer = hot standby for instant failover on peer crash\n\nCOMPACT:   profiles topic (IsCompacted=true)  →  LogCompactor.Compact(): Pass1 latest[key] wins  →  Pass2 strip tombstones (Value == null)\n            result = one msg per key · deleted keys absent  |  tombstone cancels earlier value before removal  |  new consumer replays current state from offset 0",
      "lineHeight": 1.4,
      "index": "aG",
      "frameId": null,
      "autoResize": true
    },
